{
  "text": "While the ingestion of microplastics appears to have limited effect on larvae in this study, larvae may be sensitive to the impacts of smaller plastics. In marine systems, microplastics are likely to degrade and form plastics in the nanometre range [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Nanoplastics have been shown to absorb through the chorion of fish eggs, resulting in reduced survival [CITATION_3] .",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "206771166",
